The paper deals with the problem of packing polygons, which is a classic problem in computational geometry (cs.CG). The NP-hardness result is based on a reduction from Planar-Circuit-SAT, which is a problem in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The paper also involves the use of combinatorial structures such as graphs and circuits, which are relevant to the sub-categories cs.DS and cs.DM. Finally, the problem of packing polygons has connections to the study of geometric intersection patterns, which is a topic in discrete and computational geometry (cs.GT).
